  "description" : "[h1]Project FR: Core Engine - Modern Localization Architecture[/h1]\n\n[b]Project FR: Core Engine[/b] is not just a simple translation mod. It is a [b]native technical infrastructure[/b] designed for Starbound, aimed at unifying and simplifying language management without cluttering the game's file structure.\n\n[h2]⚠️ Important Note[/h2]\n[b]This specific module is configured for the FRENCH language.[/b]\nHowever, it is built upon the [b]Project FR Core Engine[/b], a universal localization framework. If you are a developer looking to translate Starbound into another language using this high-performance architecture, please refer to the [b]\"Note to Translators\"[/b] section below.\n\n[hr][/hr]\n\n[h2]🚀 Optimized Technical Architecture:[/h2]\nWhile traditional methods rely on thousands of .patch files (which are a nightmare to maintain and often cause mod conflicts), Project FR utilizes a dynamic system:\n[list]\n[*] [b]Dynamic Tooltip Generator:[/b] I have implemented a custom [i]builder[/i] across all items. Translations are no longer \"frozen\" in a static patch; they are injected on-the-fly via a high-performance [b]caching system[/b].\n[*] [b]Centralized Dictionary:[/b] Data is grouped into a flexible, segmented structure. This engine is [b]language-agnostic by design[/b]: although configured for French, its architecture can support any language through a simple configuration change.\n[*] [b]Maximum Compatibility:[/b] By moving away from massive .patch files in favor of dynamic injection, the risk of conflicts with other mods (modifying the same objects) is drastically reduced.\n[*] [b]Data Persistence:[/b] Essential information is injected into your objects' metadata. Even if you remove the mod, items you have already acquired will retain their localized identity!\n[/list]\n\n[h2]✨ Content & Project Status (v1.0):[/h2]\n[list]\n[*] [b]Built from Scratch:[/b] To ensure a clean and organized foundation, I have rebuilt the entire Starbound localization [b]from the ground up[/b], without using obsolete bases from older mods.\n[*] [b]Full Vanilla Coverage:[/b] Over 4,000 entries processed (Items, Objects, Quests, Interfaces).\n[*] [b]Beta Phase:[/b] A massive undertaking built from zero may contain typos. The project is alive and will be refined based on your feedback!\n[*] [b]Inspection System (WIP):[/b] Currently developing a [b]Lua[/b] injection method to localize magnifying glass descriptions in a clean and universal way.\n[/list]\n\n[h2]📥 Installation & Support:[/h2]\nSubscribe and launch the game. The [b]Core Engine[/b] initializes its file routing at startup via the [i]gen_conf.config[/i] configuration file.\n[i]To report a typo or a bug, please use the \"Discussions\" tab. Including your starbound.log is always helpful![/i]\n\n[hr][/hr]\n\n[h2]🌍 Note to Translators[/h2]\n\nThe [b]Project FR[/b] architecture is \"Locale-Agnostic\". To port this engine to another language (Spanish, German, etc.):\n[list]\n[*] Simply patch the [i]gen_conf.config[/i] file to update the \"locale\" parameter.\n[*] The [i]cache system[/i] and [i]dynamic tooltip builder[/i] will automatically route requests to your new language folder.\n[/list]\n\n[hr][/hr]\n\n[h3]📜 Credits:[/h3]\n[b]Development & Architecture:[/b] Neshkel.\n[b]Legacy:[/b] Special thanks to the historical Starbound FR team (Yohann Catherine, Mickael30HG, Pho3niX, Shyning, LoGeek, Phaenix, Canarder) for their visuals and the foundation they built over 10 years ago.\n\n[b]License:[/b] Released under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0.",
